WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Mirror geometry demo.
Green X is fixed because mirror length for full-body view is half of 150 cm.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
As the viewer moves backward, d increases.
Blue Y grows following Y = 3d/(d+8).

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
At d = 2 m, Y = 60 cm.
Conclusion: X stays constant, Y increases with d.
